President Barack Obama has declared September 16th to September 22nd, 2012, as National Hispanic-Serving Institutions Week. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of providing a world-class education for the next generation and acknowledges the significant impact that postsecondary education opportunities have on the country's future, especially for Hispanic students. He praises Hispanic-Serving Institutions (HSIs) for helping make college education more accessible for Hispanic students and their families. These institutions play a critical role in American higher education by giving students access to quality education and preparing them for careers in various fields. The President also calls for a commitment to preparing future leaders and supporting institutions that equip students of all backgrounds to overcome barriers and achieve their dreams. He urges public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe National Hispanic-Serving Institutions Week with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities that recognize the contributions of these institutions and their graduates to the country.